# Documentation Rules

Never auto-edit or overwrite any file inside `docs/` unless the user explicitly asks in the current message.

If documentation needs updating due to a code change, flag it in the **Hygiene sweep** (see `bus-hygiene.mdc`) with:
`DOCS UPDATE NEEDED: [file] needs to reflect [change]`

Do not silently update docs. Always surface the required change to the user first.
DECISIONS.md is append-only — never delete or modify existing entries.
DEBUGLOG.md is append-only — never delete or modify existing entries.
